Use an information criterion (AIC or BIC) over a small grid: fit ARMA(p,q) for p,q ∈ {0,…,5} on the stationary series (difference first if needed; check ADF/KPSS) and pick the (p,q) minimizing BIC, which is preferred over AIC for n=200 because it penalizes complexity more and yields more parsimonious, consistent order selection. Cross-check with ACF/PACF of the series (PACF cutoff → AR order, ACF cutoff → MA order) and residual diagnostics (Ljung–Box p>0.05, no significant residual ACF, roots inside unit circle for invertibility/stationarity). With only 200 points, cap p+q ≤ 4–5 to avoid overfitting. In Python: `pm.auto_arima(y, d=0, max_p=5, max_q=5, seasonal=False, information_criterion='bic', stepwise=True)` or statsmodels `arma_order_select_ic(y, max_ar=5, max_ma=5, ic='bic')`.